.SH NAME
uname \- git tha name of tha current system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
\fB#include <sys/utsname.h>
.br
.sp
int uname(struct utsname *\fP\fIname\fP\fB);
.br
\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Da \fIuname\fP() function shall store shiznit identifyin the
current system up in tha structure pointed ta by
\fIname\fP.
.LP
Da \fIuname\fP() function uses tha \fButsname\fP structure defined
in \fI<sys/utsname.h>\fP.
.LP
Da \fIuname\fP() function shall return a strang namin tha current
system up in tha characta array \fIsysname\fP. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. Similarly,
\fInodename\fP shall contain tha name of dis node within a implementation-defined
communications network. Da arrays
\fIrelease\fP n' \fIversion\fP shall further identify tha operating
system. Da array \fImachine\fP shall contain a name that
identifies tha hardware dat tha system is hustlin on.
.LP
Da format of each member is implementation-defined.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.LP
Upon successful completion, a non-negatizzle value shall be returned.
Otherwise, -1 shall be returned n' \fIerrno\fP set to
indicate tha error.
.SH ERRORS
