.SH RATIONALE
.LP
Da jointz of tha structure thugz is not constrained ta have any
relation ta tha version of dis volume of
IEEE\ Std\ 1003.1-2001 implemented up in tha operatin system fo' realz. An application
should instead depend on _POSIX_VERSION and
related constants defined up in \fI<unistd.h>\fP.
.LP
This volume of IEEE\ Std\ 1003.1-2001 do not define tha sizes of
the thugz of tha structure n' permits dem ta be
of different sizes, although most implementations define dem all
to be tha same size: eight bytes plus one byte fo' tha string
terminator. Shiiit, dis aint no joke. That size fo' \fInodename\fP aint enough fo' use with
many networks.
.LP
Da \fIuname\fP() function originated up in System Pt III, System V, and
related implementations, n' it do not exist up in Version 7
or 4.3 BSD. Da joints it returns is set at system compile time in
those oldschool implementations.
.LP
4.3 BSD has \fIgethostname\fP() n' \fIgethostid\fP(), which return
a symbolic name n' a numeric value, respectively. There are
related \fIsethostname\fP() n' \fIsethostid\fP() functions dat are
used ta set tha joints tha other two functions return, so check it before ya wreck it. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. The
forma functions is included up in dis justification, tha latta are
not.
